                      label.col-md-3.inline card #
                      input.cc.inline.form-control(type='text', required='true',size='20', name='cc-number', x-autocompletetype='cc-number', data-stripe='number', placeholder='####-####-####-####')
                  .form-group.col-sm-6
                      label.col-md-3.inline cvc
                      input.col-sm-3.inline.form-control(type='text', required='true',size='4',name='cc-cvc', x-autocompletetype='cc-csc', data-stripe='cvc', placeholder='###')
                .row
                  .form-group.col-sm-6
                    .row
                      .col-xs-12
                        label.col-md-3 expiration
                    .row
                      .col-xs-6
                        input.inline.form-control(type='text', required='true',size='2', name='cc-exp-month', data-stripe='exp-month', placeholder='mm')
                      .col-xs-6
                        input.inline.form-control(type='text', required='true',size='4', name='cc-exp-year', data-stripe='exp-year', placeholder='yyyy')
                .row
                  .form-group.col-sm-6
                    .row
                      .col-xs-12
                        label.col-md-3 model 
                        select.model.input-lg.form-control(name='version')
                          option(value='257.78') original $250
                          option(value='180.54') plank $175
                          option(value='103.30') kit $100
                    .row.model-descriptions
                      .col-xs-12
                        label.col-md-12 description
                        strong.tight the original, it puts the <span style='font-weight: bolder;font-variant:small-caps;font-size:20px;'>&quot;block&quot;</span> in clockblock. this model is three boards thick and approximately 11" x 11" x 2.75". it feels good and massive in your hands.
                      .col-xs-12.hidden
                        label.col-md-12 description
                        strong.tight the plank, its the <span style='font-weight: bolder;font-variant:small-caps;font-size:20px;'>slimmer</span> cousin of the original. plank is a single board thick and approximately 11" x 11" x .75". it takes us significantly less time to produce, hence the lower cost.
                      .col-xs-12.hidden
                        label.col-md-12 description
                        strong.tight the kit, fancy yourself a <span style='font-weight: bolder;font-variant:small-caps;font-size:20px;'>DIY</span> kind of person. well we made this one just for you... we didn't finish it! you'll receive a populated pcb, some wires, some screws, and a plank. oh i guess instructions too...
                  .col-sm-6
